@mengxr this `NOTICE` is not quite correct.

`netlib-core` is released under a 3 clause BSD, which I believe _is_ compatible with Apache. Although you should check this to be comfortable.

However, use of the `netlib-all` (i.e. native) components is optional and will pull in both LGPL libraries and machine-specific libraries that use arbitrary (potentially highly commercially sensitive) licenses (e.g. Intel Math Kernel Library)
